  {
    "date": "2026-03-01",
    "head_line": "A day of leeks and legends",
    "title": "St Davids Cathedral, Pembrokeshire, Wales",
    "copyright": "© Terence Waeland/Alamy",
    "desc": "1 March is the day Wales politely clears its throat and makes its point. No fireworks, no fanfare—just hymns, dragons and a nation confidently wearing vegetables. Saint David's Day celebrates Welsh identity with quiet pride and a good sense of humour. Saint David was a 6th-century preacher and monastic founder whose advice to 'do the little things' still does the rounds on banners, mugs and moral compasses.",
